<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Buck</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Buck reports that altogether about 22,000 men have been ordered
                                to China by the Japanese Government.)</p>
